title: A NIGHT IN THE LIFE: Jon Hendricks
description:
One musician, one night: Jazz at Lincoln Center's A NIGHT IN THE LIFE is a documentary series that gives you a revealing look behind the curtain of a jazz musician's life. 

Jazz at Lincoln Center is deeply saddened by the recent passing of Jon Hendricks at the age of 96. We were fortunate to have the opportunity to sit down with this legendary artist recently. In this episode, vocalist JON HENDRICKS gets ready for his birthday show at Minton's and reminisces about his strong bond with Thelonious Monk.

Director: Brandon Bain
Producer: Eugenia Han
Editor: Sophia Pike Betz
Graphic Designer: Brian Welesko
Production Assistants: Richard Emery & Jonathan Fricke

In loving memory of Jon & Judith Hendricks

Subscribe to our channel: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCP108sGgYT_TlG2YRColGcg?sub_confirmation=1

For more information on Jazz at Lincoln Center: http://jazz.org/
